The City Management is committed to:
     Preventing accidents;
     Training our employees in correct response procedures in the event of an accident;
     Providing leadership to the community with respect to emergency preparedness;
     Addressing any citizen concerns by fully explaining potential hazrds associated with facility operations;
     Taking the necessary steps to prevent and mitigate accidents; and
     Being a good corporate citizen of Jefferson County.
With these objectives in mind, the Risk Management Plan provides information about the City's management of the risk associated with the chlorine water treatment process, but more importantly stresses the commitment to ensuring a safe operation for employees, visitors, and community.
